05/09/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- OSCE's chairman-in-office, Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy, has appointed Czech diplomat Pavel Vacek, as the new head of the OSCE Presence in Albania. 
Vacek, who succeeds Finnish diplomat Osmo Lipponen, will take up the post on 1 October. 
(OSCE web site - 03/09/04)
